  "id": "019d33f6-ba49-7df2-8b14-3008e789b948",
  "content": "# BM25 Hybrid Search Phase 3: Integration + Hot-Swap -- Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: ArcSwap hot-swap for RAG pipeline, graceful degradation, config hot-reload wiring.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. AppState.rag uses Arc<ArcSwap<RagPipeline>> for zero-downtime pipeline swap. load() returns Guard for request-scoped snapshot isolation. Matches existing HNSW ArcSwap pattern from PR #30.\n2. Config lock released before pipeline rebuild to avoid blocking concurrent config reads during I/O-heavy TantivyIndex open + component construction.\n3. Generator preserved across hot-swaps by loading current_generator from old pipeline before rebuild. Without this, ask() mode breaks after any pipeline swap.\n4. Embedding failure degrades to BM25-only when non-embedding searchers exist (needs_embedding() trait method). All-searchers-fail returns error instead of silent empty results.\n5. Old pipeline deferred drop via std::thread::spawn(move || drop(old)) after ArcSwap::swap(), matching the HNSW deallocation pattern.\n6. PipelineRegistry::validate_and_build() validates config before swap. Invalid config rejected with error, old pipeline continues. Error surfaced in config_set response as pipeline_error field.\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- Single-searcher fast path (no tokio::spawn) lacks panic isolation. Multi-searcher path catches panics via JoinHandle. Known gap, acceptable for now.\n- config_set writes to disk before pipeline rebuild. If rebuild fails, config on disk may reference settings not matching the running pipeline. Acceptable trade-off since server restart will attempt the same config.\n- validate_and_build silently degrades on partial searcher failures (some fail, some succeed). Warnings logged but not surfaced to MCP caller beyond pipeline_swapped field.\n\n## What Blocked:\n- Clippy collapsible_if lint required let-chains syntax for the pipeline key check + ArcSwap pattern match. Minor style adjustment.",
